During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki provided updates on various topics. She mentioned a new report that found the tax reform proposals in President Biden's American Families Plan would affect less than 1 percent of U.S. taxpayers. Psaki also outlined the President's upcoming schedule, including a trip to Yorktown, Virginia, and remarks on the COVID-19 response and the economy. In response to questions, Psaki discussed the CDC's announcement on a possible July 1st reopening for New York City, the completion of the North Korea policy review, a potential meeting between President Biden and President Putin, and the administration's efforts to assist India with COVID-19 relief. She also addressed vaccine misinformation, the decrease in the number of minors in CBP detention facilities, and the Title 42 policy. Psaki mentioned the administration's approach to combating vaccine hesitancy and misinformation and stated that they are evaluating what further steps may be needed.